cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about human pose estimation from videos using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep structured model that can be efficiently trained in an end-to-end manner, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the incorporation of domain knowledge about the human body into the network suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of the proposed approach on two widely used benchmarks for video-based pose estimation suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
